near tokyo originally planning to reach san diego yokohamas 
sister city in about four days by hitching a ride on the 
highaltitude jet stream winds that generally blow eastward 
but the winds were blowing north toward alaska forcing niwa to 
stay at a lower altitude his spokesmen have said 
saturday afternoon niwa suffered severe sickness from the rough 
seas but he recovered by the time he was rescued said kenji 
fukawa another spokesman for the balloonist 
niwa at one point opened a window at the top of his globeshaped 
capsule to get fresh air to combat the seasickness he also shone a 
beam of light into the open sea with a flashlight after dark to help 
rescuers spot him fukawa said 
the fishing boat was guided to the site by one of two government 
p3c patrol planes the other one flew over niwas gondola to 
monitor his position 
attempts to rescue him in a seaplane failed the government sent 
a us1 seaplane but it returned with engine problems a second us1 
proved useless because it arrived after dark 
the fishing boat initially was delayed by 30mph winds which 
later diminished 
niwa an experienced balloonist quit his job with a computer 
firm three months ago to prepare for the journey 
in 1981 four balloonists successfully crossed the pacific ocean 
by balloon for the first time no one has traveled the distance 
alone 
