moderate afghan groups are pushing for 
the restoration of afghanistans last king as the only way to avoid 
a bloody struggle between rival guerrilla groups 
but powerful fundamentalist parties among moslem guerrillas 
fighting the afghan government say they will never allow the return 
of the monarchy 
king zahir shah who was deposed in 1973 is the only afghan 
leader who enjoys broad support that cuts across party tribal and 
ethnic lines according to some afghan exiles and analysts 
the 74yearold king who lives in exile in rome is the one 
figure who may be able to unite a majority of afghans in the deeply 
divided nation they say 
people think the king is the only person who can command the 
support of the entire nation and form the broadest possible 
