<TEXT>
its been nearly a century since a 
typewriter salesman with poor eyesight founded the coleman co now 
his descendants are fighting to ensure the family name not only 
stays on the products but runs the boardroom 
led by wc colemans grandson who is the companys chief 
executive and a parttime rocknroll musician members of the 
coleman clan have made a 64 per share debtfinanced takeover offer 
for the worldfamous maker of camping gear 
analysts say the 332 million deal could be a defensive move to 
fend off other takeover bids for the corporation that had record 
sales of 6579 million and record earnings of 245 million in 1988 
the coleman saga began in 1899 when wc working on a wintry 
night in brockton ala saw a bright steady light coming from a 
drugstore window startled he trudged across a muddy street and 
discovered the store had a lamp that burned gasoline under pressure 
and used a mantle instead of a wick 
unlike the flickering wickfed kerosene lamps and dim carbon 
filament electric bulbs the lamp threw light that enabled the 
typewriter salesman to see well at night for the first time in his 
adult life he could even read the apothecary jar labels on the 
stores shelves 
coleman investigated to see where the lamp came from and got 
territorial sales rights and later production rights for it 
leasing lamps and maintaining them coleman developed a company 
that he moved to wichita in his native kansas from kingfisher okla 
in 1901 
he figured out his real product was light not lamps so he 
sold lighting service said craig miner a wichita state 
university history instructor who is working on a book about the 
company 
by 1914 the company developed the coleman lantern and has since 
sold more than 40 million it was called the sunshine of the 
night and was credited with lengthening farmers days 
products ranging from lanters to fuelheated irons and coffee 
pots brought the company success but wc coleman wasnt a business 
management genius and couldnt keep the company out of trouble 
during the great depression 
wcs son robert sheldon who went by his middle name stepped 
in and reorganized the companys finances by 1932 it was in good 
health again though lanterns and campstoves remained big sellers 
sheldon coleman diversified into oil space heaters and gas floor 
furnaces coleman became a major exporter 
the coleman gi stove which went from concept to production in 
60 days was called one of the most important pieces of noncombat 
equipment in world war ii it would operate on whatever fuel was 
available and in weather ranging from 125 degrees farenheit to 60 
below 
coleman lighting was so well known to americans that a battle of 
the bulge password was based on that familiarity sentries would 
call out the challenge coleman and wait for the answer lamp 
from approaching soldiers 
but by 1960 coleman was weakening again its total markets had 
declined 70 percent and another diversification push started this 
time into outdoor recreation products 
one million lanterns still are sold annually but dozens of other 
items ranging from tents to sleeping bags coolers to ski vests 
have made coleman the top manufacturer of outdoor recreation 
products worldwide 
it makes knives airguns boats canoes water skis popup 
travel trailers emergency electric generators lawn mowers and home 
and recreational vehicle heating and air conditioning equipment 
new products are the lifeblood of our company said don 
berchtold coleman co executive vice president 
robert sheldon colemans son sheldon c coleman spent some of 
his early adult years in business in california and was a 
temporary disappointment to the family historian miner said 
even when he later joined the companys management he was most 
often seen in blue jeans a casual shirt and jogging shoes mingling 
with the similarly clad employees in the outing products division he 
successfully headed 
sheldon c clearly wasnt exactly the threepiece suit 
buttondown collar type of executive and that was a change for the 
traditionally conservative company miner said 
as his alterego dewey he plays guitar and sings in a 
rocknroll band called dewey and the big dogs he also owns a small 
recording studio and nightclub called big dog studio sound stage 
it reminds me of malcom forbes who rides motorcycles and hot 
air balloons said miner those just arent the kinds of things 
you expect the ceo of a major company to do 
sheldon c coleman 36 assumed the company presidency in 1987 
became chief executive officer in 1988 and was elected chairman 
following his fathers death at 86 on sept 21 
although some analysts have speculated the takeover proposal is 
sheldon cs way of putting the company on the market a company 
insider who asked not to be identified said the coleman clan is 
committed to retaining control 
hed tell you that in a second but the lawyers would probably 
kill him the anonymous coleman executive said 
